      <head>Siegmund von Hausegger</head>

      <div>
        <p>Austrian conductor, teacher, and writer on music.</p>
        
        <p>Hausegger's career as a conductor began in Munich in 1899, continuing in Frankfurt
          (1903-06), Hamburg and Berlin (1910-). In 1920, he was appointed Director, later
          President, of the Akademie der Tonkunst in Munich, and in 1925 became the President of the
          Allgemeiner Deutscher Musikverein. Hausegger was also a composer of operas, orchestral
          works and vocal music.</p>
      </div>
